reviews_data.review_text: Great quality! Unfortunately seems like you have to get there early enough otherwise you they run out… definitely coming back A++

Just discovered this cafe in Huntersville, and I am in awe! It is an “Artisan French Bakery” and man do they deliver! I’ve been to France before and everything they serve is authentic. The decor is very cute, the process is smooth, and the vibe is chill. They have nice music playing as well. But the star is their food! My mother and I both got a breakfast croissant with bacon, egg, and cheese. My mom is generally hard to please as it relates to food, and she was wholly impressed. Her statement, “This may be the best breakfast croissant I’ve ever had.” Their offerings are varied, beautiful and tasty. And the lattes are excellent as well. 10/10 recommend and I can’t wait to return to try more!
Incredible French Bakery ❤️ I had the raspberry croissant, To Die For‼️

My wife and I absolutely loved Paris, France. Since returning, we have not found a place to give us a similar feel until we stopped here! A must try, baguettes, croissants, all the delicious eats you could imagine from France.
The food and selection are great! Need to time it right or the ordering process is a bit chaotic.
Great food at great prices

Food is great but pricey. Coffee is not good at ALL! Have many moms with kiddos who stays way too long so the atmosphere could be chaos and super noisy. Service is bad, dont ask for anything as they will be rude
excellent, that's it just freaking excellent
Delicious pastries and foods. Nice splurge on occasion.
Best bakery in the area
The best bakery I have found in the area! If you are gluten sensitive this is the place for you!!!!!

I was expecting another mid quiche that was soggy and overpriced but I was wrong. No one in charlotte area does quiche like this place. Coffee was delicious, didn’t try their pastries but they looked incredible. This is the perfect place to take your mom when she’s in town.
I love the New York Roll, and I've liked everything I've tried
One too many delicious vegetarian options to choose from. Caprese sandwich with tomato red pepper basil bisque was a hit! Highly recommend!
Love this place. Amazing coffee and the best vibes 🤍

I come here for the croissants.  However, don’t even think about asking to have it cut in half & toasted because that throws the staff into an absolute tailspin of confusion.  This simple task took (literally) 10+ minutes and likely only happened ‘at all’ because I had to stand at the counter asking where my order was - which clearly annoyed the girl at the register. When I asked if  someone could else check on it, I was told by another staff member, it only takes 2 minutes to toast 😳🤯. Exactly! It should only take about two minutes - so why have I been standing here for 12 minutes!? Like what?!  NO apology for the inconvenience. Made me feel like “I” was the problem. Probably never going back.  Not worth my frustration.
Cute little patisserie
This place is *Chef's kiss! Yum!

Great bakery that delivers excellent goods and service. I love their whole grain sourdough breads. The cakes and pastries look incredible. The staff really strives to please. The ambiance and look of the place is charming and on point. All around , Cocotte is a great addition to Cornelius.
Had lunch at Cocotte and it absolutely delivered. Fresh ingredients, bold flavors, and everything felt thoughtfully made.
Excellent French style pastries, sandwiches.  The Parisian as good as Paris and the pumpkin pie better than mom’s!

This is a really nice spot. Just has a perfect friendly welcoming vibe and a lot of great looking stuff.

The breakfast sandwich has some room for improvement. Good croissant, but seemed a little lacking with what they put in it. Still, the rest of the baked goods they have available are great.

Worth a shout.

We stopped by for the first time on Saturday and ended up trying a whole spread — The Caprese, The Parisian, The Lox Avocado, hot chocolate, chai latte, cappuccino, Pain Suisse, crème brûlée bun, and a cinnamon roll. Literally everything was fresh, flavorful, and made with care.

The pastries were insane (that crème brûlée bun… wow), and the sandwiches were super fresh and really well put together. Drinks were great too — cozy, not overly sweet, just right.

The service was friendly and the whole place had that warm, welcoming vibe you want from a bakery. We’ll definitely be back soon!
Beautiful French bakery - BUSY - get here  early! Tons of coffee and latte options and outdoor dining areas perfect for warmer weather. Kid friendly!
Great staff. Product looks like a magazine photo. Expensive. Tried a number of different products. Hit or miss. Mostly a hit though.
There is no better.  The quality of the food is impeccable.

This spot is so legit, the pastries are stunning and expertly made. Aesthetically immaculate, quality and taste is unlike other baked goods in the area. You cannot beat the scope of what they have to offer, in addition to the breakfast sandwich which is a very simple and elegant bacon, egg, and cheese on a croissant. Coffee program is solid, but definetly pastry and bakery forward, would highly recommend for a breakfast excursion!
An Amazing Culinary find right here in the Huntersville - Cornelius Area! Hands down best French Bakery & Croissants in all of Charlotte! Don’t miss out put on this Gem!
Desserts and pastries looked so perfect I thought they were display food, very tasty sandwiches.

Sacre Bleu! Stopped on our way home from Charlotte and this bakery did not disappoint. Had the best breakfast crossaint ever and picked up a few other pastries along with a sour dough bread to take home. Great service too. So good!
Love this place! Great breads, breakfast sandwich, and amazing desserts! Best around!!!
Deliciousness!!!!
Everything is great but the swiss cheese sourdough is so delicious!
Great bakery! Very friendly team. Lots of great options to choose from. Definitely will be returning.
Amazing. C'est manifique!

This place has no systematic order to the actual ordering process. When you are in line it isn’t clear the process or who is taking your order. It is very confusing as to who is taking your order or who you pay etc. it is chaos. I have been twice and both times same experience with this. Food is good. Those baking should wear caps or hats to keep hair out of food. Hope it gets better. Lots of potential.
Great coffee and pastries! All fresh, a little pricey but worth it!

My husband and I came in for breakfast and coffee and we ended up buying that, 7 other pastries, 2 loafs of bread, and 2 jars of the homemade pestos. Everything was fresh and absolutely amazing. As sweet as everything looks, it's not overwhelming, the sandwiches were to die for and the coffee was perfect! I will be coming back as often as I can. We love this place! 💕

Great food and pastries.
Very unorganized service wise, but very worth the wait!
I just went here for the first time, and everything was excellent. I can't wait to go back!
Friendly staff.  Amazing desserts
Очень  вкусное выпечка 😋

The baguette is not quite what I was expecting, it was not very crunchy , that means it is missing an important step on baking: water spray, so the baguette can develop very crunchy crust.

Also, the coffee is dark roast and for the wrong and bitter beans. I would recommend medium roast or a.more coarser grind.
This is the real deal. Authentic French pastry at its finest.
The food is great! Love it. Got an incredibly good cafe au lait also.
The breads and pastries were fantastic, I wanted to take more home. The line was a bit long but it was well worth the time.

It's all right. The pastry is the only good thing they have. The coffees are ok. I've had better coffee cups in other places. I can tell the ingredients some are local. The salmon sandwich is average not that great. The kids sandwich is even better to be honest. The soup they have is average. Very expensive place. Spent like 120
dollars and it was not worth the money.
Atmosphere was like any other coffee shop. Their staff was wearing French outfits.
Service ok.
Staff seems to be on another channel with orders, they charge me for pastry, then I had to go back to pay for the other food and a female told me you gotta pay first before eat, it sounded very stupid to say something like that.
So I had to go back to the register and pay in cash and they were not that organized.
Lines are too long,  waiting 30 min for service
Unique bakery and restaurant, tons of options and good coffee too. A French flavor/theme - we had an enjoyable experience and plan to return.
Over priced. Pastry is not sweet enough. I have tried almost every pastry they serve. Not enough filling in pastries.
Excellent "boulangère".  A wee bit on the expensive side but IMHO to be expected (we are not in France).  I will be back!
Everything we tried was fantastic! We'll be going back often, I'm sure.

reviews_data.review_text: Made daily

Stopped in today for the first time. Gorgeous little bakery. Wonderfully friendly atmosphere and service Lived in Europe for a number of years and spent loads of time in Paris and Southern France. A beautifully done replication of the experience there. Beautiful presentation of baked goods. We tried croissants, tarts and a sourdough loaf. All outstanding. May seem a bit pricey at first but once you taste the baked goods you will likely say "oh, I get it now!". Already planning our next trip to try sandwiches and to buy more bread and sweet goods.
Nice place. Cute French vibe.  Desserts were light and delicious. They need two registers. Line was too long with just one.
Everything is delicious, excellent quality breads, it is difficult to choose just one.
Great pastry, especially some of the savory croissants. Lots of seating, indoor and outdoor and a large area for kids to play!

It's a cute place with a lot of food options including gluten-free ones! Loved the macarons, chocolate chip cookies, and the chai latte I got.

Ordering is a little chaotic with all the hustle and bustle, but once you get someone, they stay with you along the counter.

Lots of seating is available.
Great sandwiches,  desserts,  coffee and service.  Friendly staff!!
The best!
Very busy Saturday morning

Took my parents out to try a bakery in the area, and this place did not disappoint at all!

The people here are very nice, and the food and beverages are delicious. I personally recommend the Charlotte for anyone who goes here—it has hazelnut sponge cake base with raspberry cream.

11/10 recommend!

Taste of France without TSA!
Walk in and find (or create!) your memory of France via scent!  The food and hospitality is amazing!!!!!  The owners moved their family to LKN, USA to fulfill their dream & commitment to family💟 We appreciate you and your team!
Cocotte is such a charming bakery! The pastries are always fresh and delicious. A special thanks to Jenny for her kind and attentive service – she makes every visit even better!

Don’t know why I never noticed this place before. As someone born and raised in Europe😅, the croissants here actually gave me a little home feeling lol. Definitely not like the basic grocery store croissants these are legit good.

They even had some of that viral stuff you see online, like cube or rolled croissants. 🥐 They’re really good, just a bit pricier than normal, but honestly that’s alright ’cause they hit.

Sorry for the pic btw, I had to take a bite out of one first lol
Delicious food baked fresh daily!
The best bakery I’ve been to in North Carolina, the pastries are incredible and taste just as good as they look.

If you want hair in your bread,  this is the place to go. Called to let them know and someone answered rudely and disregard my comments 😒.

Service not the best, the cashier had a " hate being here look", asked for extra tape for my boxed which she disregard  and hand me my receipt as she was looking at the next customer in line.
So cute and the food is delicious! Definitely will come back frequently.

review_questions.Group size: 1 person, 2 people, 3-4 people, Suitable for all group sizes

reviews_data.review_text: It was our first time visiting and we will definitely be back any time we are in the area. The croissants were indescribably good and the fresh loaves of bread were truly works of art. The staff made us feel welcome and the atmosphere made us want to return when we can stay longer. Truly a gem.
Great spot, nice owners and fantastic food. Solid go to for the weekends with the family.

Visited for the first time. Grabbed a sandwich and side chick pea salad. Very good. Simple assembly line type of ordering. Menu had more selections than I anticipated. Very nice space inside and out.  I did not have any of the desserts or bread which they are known for, so I suspect the food rating might be higher when I do partake. And also heard the coffee is top shelf

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Quiche, Apple Turnover Croissant, Fruit Salad

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped in for coffee, breakfast, and a pastry! Coffee was delicious! Breakfast filled us up & the fruit was very fresh. The apple turnover croissant was not only beautifully made, but it was absolutely delicious. Will definitely come back. Thanks for the great customer service.
BEST BAKERY!!! Pastries and breads that taste even better than they look. Our whole family loves their breakfast croissants as well.
So thrilled there’s a French bakery in town!

Wow! What beautiful pastries and treats! Mesmerizing for the eyes and divine for the nose. We tried the Apple bow tie, Madeline’s, Olive and Rosemary baguette, of course chocolate croissants! And tasty coffee treats ☕️ Heading back tomorrow morning. A must try!

This is by far the best addition to the Lake Norman area. The coffee selection and quality is amazing. The food and pastry options are delicious! Anytime friends come to town. This is our new go to place
Attention dog owners. No pup cups.
This place is the real deal when it comes to bakeries. Everything I’ve tried has been delicious and you can tell it’s made by hand.
Incredible! The croissants are amazing and everything I have tried has been wonderful! So happy to have this lovely French bakery in Cornelius!

A truly authentic French patisserie - so glad we have one here in the Lake Norman area! The pastries and breads made here are top notch - you’d be pressed to find this level of quality outside of a high-end European cafe this side of the Atlantic. The staff are friendly and the atmosphere is inviting. On the weekends there is always a line outside. The wait is 100% worth it!

Dirty and Rude – Won’t Be Returning

We visited this bakery and were immediately put off by flies all over the place, including near the food. Not a good look for a place selling items you’re supposed to eat.

My son picked something he didn’t enjoy, and I politely asked the owner if we could simply exchange it — not for a refund, just a simple swap for something even less expensive. She flat-out refused. No understanding, no effort to help, not even for a child.

Between the lack of cleanliness and the unfriendly, inflexible attitude, we’ll never be back. Do better.

Everything is great here. Just pick anything.
Best croissants in town.
Best damn lemon meringue pie slice I ever had.
Wonderful pastries and the staff are always so kind and friendly! It’s hard to get out without spending a chunk of change, but it’s so worth it for quality baked goods and coffee.
The best bread in the area

So disappointed in Cocotte. I ordered the Caprese and the baguette was so hard and difficult to chew. The inside was soggy and the spinach was bitter. I understand baguettes are usually crispy on the outside and soft on the inside but this one was not enjoyable. The chickpea salad was bland.
I also ordered the Charlotte and the raspberry was too tart and the topped blueberries were sour. The food does not taste as good as it is presented. The wait time was long and the ordering process is unorganized. I probably won’t be going back.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Marcie

We wanted to let you know that we had to make an exceptional modification to the apple bowtie filling on Sunday. Unfortunately, the result wasn’t up to our usual standards, and we truly regret that. We’ve decided to pause serving this croissant until we can return to our original recipe—and we’d love for you to try it again when it's back to its best!

Regarding the rustic baguette: we appreciate your note and will definitely pay closer attention to the baking time. It’s meant to be a crunchy bread, but certainly not hard as you experienced.

Your feedback helps us improve, and we’re grateful for your support!
reviews_data.review_text:
Tried a few items. Very disappointed in the Apple Bow Tie. I was expecting delicious baked apples in the middle not what appeared and tasted like apple sauce (picture provided.) The Lox Avocado on a rustic baguette was so hard we had an issue cutting into it and chewing it. It was so hard we had to take it home and warm up a bagel to enjoy the smoked salmon we paid for. Overall the place is good for what's available in the area, but not the best I've had.
Recommend: Chocolate Croissant, Breakfast Sandwich, and Chocolate Chunk Cookie
I stopped by today and ordered the daily special - a peach croissant. It was spectacular!!!

Sandwich and soup were awesome and the pistachio macaroon was amazing! We will be back to try more :). The line/checkout was odd though. They need two checkout stations to manage who goes to checkout in line.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Caitlin,  thank you for your feedback. We apologize if the ordering process was not clear. When you arrive at the beginning of the line a vendor will welcome you to take your order (pastries, sandwiches, quiches and beverages), the fresh baked bread is usually picked at the end of the line as this is where it is display. 
We also had 4 new hiring in the past couple of weeks, and today was the first and second day for 2 of our new front of the house team member! We appreciate your patience and understanding as we're all doing our best to serve you efficiently, especially on busy days like today ;)
reviews_data.review_text: Pastries and bread are delicious. The ordering system is inefficient and not entirely clear - the staff could be friendlier and help guide customers through the line. For example: no one asked for a coffee order so we assumed we order it at the register. Multiple staff people were clearly annoyed when we did so.

Our family loves to visit Cocotte.  They have excellent sandwiches, pastries, breads, and more!  The owner, Angela, is so kind and goes out of her way to take care of her customers.  Cocotte makes everything from scratch so you know it’s good.  They use French flour and many of their ingredients are imported from Europe.  You are getting a real taste of France when you come here!

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Merci Jinny!!!
All of our team, pastry and baker chefs work everyday on providing only fresh and delicious baked goodies! The front of the house is there to welcome you and present all the beautiful products they made. 
We're happy to be your local bakery and coffeeshop! And we're always happy to see you late afternoon Jinny 😉
reviews_data.review_text: Every single item I have tasted is amazing! Not only delicious beyond words the pastries and breads are beautiful in presentation. So happy to have a Cocotte in the neighborhood.
The new spot when me and my step sister want pastries
The afternoon we went there wasn't much of anything available. The bread looked very inviting but very expensive.

Legit good bakery. You know it by the way it smells when you walk in. It's the only European style bakery that I can think of in the Lake Norman area. Everything is fresh baked, the staff are friendly, and there is a ton of space both indoor and out. The coffee is quite good as well. I look forward to returning!

As a French family, we felt right at home!
This pastry shop is in a great location, the service is exceptional, and the chef pâtissier is both kind and truly talented.
The sandwiches and pastries are top-notch — magnifique!
A true taste of France.
Highly recommended!
Real authentic French bakery! Simply the best.
The best pastries!

reviews_data.owner_answer: Merci Ina! We're happy to bring a little piece of France in Lake Norman and glad to read you enjoyed it! A Bientôt.
reviews_data.review_text: The location is perfect, and the atmosphere is like walking into a Paris bakery. The staff is welcoming.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you Jessie for your feedback! 
The past few days were really busy with the holiday and 3 new front of the house team in training! We knew some mistakes happened, and we apologize about it. We appreciate a lot your understanding! As we know your first won't be the last, we'll be happy to offer you your beverage next time you swing by ;)
reviews_data.review_text:
For my first visit, I picked up a few pastries to take home and a tea latte. The number of choices was a bit overwhelming, to be honest!

I did have to wait a good bit for my drink, extra because of an error with the drink, actually twice, but I didn't correct the second error because I needed to get home.

But, the time I waited gave me a chance to browse the for sale items, outside of the bakery items, and the variety of seating, including a children's area with some toys and books.  At least one booth had a plug if you need to work for a bit and there is Wi-Fi.

I was excited to see a place with a variety of tea and tea lattes; however, the seasonal latte I ordered was first given to me as an iced coffee. I don't drink coffee, so I asked to correct the drink. I was given an iced tea drink that was OK BUT it was not a latte. No milk!

The best pastries I tried were the apple bow tie and blueberry brioche bun. The chocolate cream croissant didn't have much filling and the lemon meringue pie slice had kind of a sticky texture?

Some of the items are a reasonable price but others are a little on the high side, so my review is a little mixed.
🤩 wow, what a find! C’est manufique!! If you want authentic French breads and amazing pastries and desserts, come here. They have so many options. Gotta go again!

C’est magnifique!!

Cinq étoiles!!
The best pastries I’ve ever had. Everything looks so good, the decision is overwhelming.
Best breads and pastries! 🥐🥖🍞🍰😋
Everything is absolutely delicious here!
Unbelievable bakery with the most delicious chocolate croissant it was gone in 30 seconds.

We absolutely love Cocotte!  I stopped in to grab some pastries on Saturday for Mother's Day and although there was a line, it moved quickly. I picked up a couple almond croissant (light,  flaky & wonderful almond flavor), a few macaroons (scrumptious) and a couple of eclairs (yummy chocolate-WOW!).  Once I arrived home (around 4:00), I decided to place an online order for a couple of cinnamon rolls and chocolate croissants to pick up the following morning. Unfortunately, they did not have this available as I missed the 12:00 cut off (completely my fault!)  They were more than gracious to offer a refund or a choice of other pastry items. Of course, I chose the pastry items, and I have to say they over-compensated for MY mistake!  Needless to say, everything was incredibly fresh and delicious. Such lovely, friendly & accommodating staff and mouthwatering baked goods. We used to drive down to Charlotte for fresh French pastries. So glad we have this incredible gem in Cornelius now!!

Absolutely exceptional. You can tell they really take pride in everything they do and the ingredients they use. The pastries are fantastic and look immaculate. We have tried multiple different drinks and they have all been very good. Once you go once you will keep going back.

Food was really disappointing. I felt fooled that the pictures made everything look so good. All of the sandwiches were pre-made and kept in a refrigerator which makes the bread go extremely hard and chewy. Ive had airport sandwiches that tasted fresher. If the food was prepared to order as the menu makes it seem it could probably be 10x better. The chickpea side salad was oily and bland. Pastry was dry and tasted 2 days old and the custard had such an artificial taste behind it. We barely ate any of the food and it wasn't cheap. Service was slow and unhelpful too. This place has potential as the customer vibe was good and the bread loaves looked great but refrigerating the pre-made sandwiches is ruining it.
Awesome food and great service!

Love this place! The coffee, every pastry and OMG the quiche is like no other I've ever had. Can't seem to go wrong with anything I've had from there. Also, I recommend getting there early, they do run out.

There was a long hair in my pastry, I asked to get it replaced - no apology whatsoever. Then I went to the bathroom, and when I came out they threw out my drink that I only took one sip of. I'm pissed.
Excellent bakery

There is a place for kids to play with toys or read. My grandkids are 1 and almost 3 years old and stay entertained for hours. They get a chance to play with other kids. Also patio to sit outside. Food choices are amazing treats.

I love Cocotte, definitely my weekend goto when I’m out and about. Every time I go, I want to order everything. There Almond Croissants are 10 out of 10, and the Gourmand Twist is my favorite. Everything I tried has been worthy and not overly sweet; the way I like it. If you’re in the area - definitely checkout this little hidden gem for coffee, tea, desserts, etc.
The best bakery Ever!!!!
Best croissants .

Oh my goodness if you haven't been here then you are missing out on some awesome French baking! Their croissants are to die for so buttery and flaky! And the bread well I've tried just about all of it and I just can't name a favorite. Because they are all so so good. Especially with my homemade honey butter.
Best of the best if you are looking for true authentic French Bakery!! Second to none!

reviews_data.review_text: I was in ❤️ with all I purchased
Traditional French bakery in Cornelius, decent coffee and great croissants along with soup and sandwich selection for lunch.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Croissant Selection, Apple Turnover Croissant, Nutella Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: Meet a friend for a latte and pear tart, Amazing! I took home cheese bread loaf, 3 different croissants, and a Gluten free cupcake. Everything was awesome!❤️❤️❤️
Food was great.  Prices was expensive.  Including 15pct tip, it was 23 for 2 packs of 4 cookies
Absolutely fantastic desserts!
This is the first place I have found in the North Charlotte area that is worthy of being called a “bakery.” They have real bread and a variety of pastries too!

Everything about it is wonderful! The pastries and quiche are delicious, it’s clean, and the atmosphere is inviting. They are so friendly and did I say the pastries were delicious!! They really look too beautiful to eat.

We really needed this place in our area, I hope they have so much success. We sat and talked for about two hours and there was a steady line of customers so it looks like they’re off to a good start.

Authentic, delish! We can’t wait to go back. My husband said, “the longer we sit here the weaker my self control will become.” Loved: croque monsieur + soup of the day, Nutella croissant (perfectly light and not too sweet, tastes like chocolate mousse filling), pear croissant, cinnamon roll, gourmet fruit and cream twist thing. HIGHLY RECOMMEND.

What a true, authentic French bakery. If you are looking for fast food, this is not the place. The owners and bakers are masters of their craft and deliver a wonderful experience.  We have also ordered many custom catering orders for other offices and the feedback from the Doctors/ Staff have been amazing. Thank you for coming to Cornelius!
So delicious! Service is amazing.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Pan Au Chocolat, Strawberry Fruit Tart, Croissant Selection, Apple Turnover Croissant, Bacon Egg Cheese Croissant, Croissant and Double Espresso, Lemon Curd Croissant to Go, Lemons Curd Croissant Inside, Chocolate Chip Cookie, Quiche, Cinnamon Roll

reviews_data.review_text: This is a Saturday morning must for espresso and croissant! Everything is amazing!

The slice of Quiche Lorraine was bigger than the Veggie one, even though both have the same price. There was too much cheese and not too many eggs. The color seemed too white, unless you use egg whites mostly. I make my own Quiche weekly and its color is very yellow.

The pastries of this place are like no other, total perfection. We did not have a real bakery in this area and I am delighted that Cocotte opened here. I truly believe that the mediocre reviews done here are posted by some competition bakery. Someone mentioned they couldn't find anything with cinnamon? You can find cinnamon pretty much in everything in the U.S, so for that you can go to get a pastry at any supermarket. Cocotte is the closest to a real French bakery that you can find in Cornelius/Huntersville, NC.
My first visiting! I tastes their croissant at a cafe near my house. So I wanted to visit the bakery!! So many choices here, it was hard to choose one! I will be back soon~ pleasant experience!
Delicious

reviews_data.owner_answer: Bonjour Kim, we're happy to read you loved our food! To answer your comment about the service, I'd like you to understand that the person who served you started on Saturday. Assuming you swung by this weekend, it was probably her first or second day at the bakery. We usually do not ask our hundreds of customers their choice of milk (we default to whole milk if not specified). As for the 10 minute wait on your custom breakfast sandwich, this is the time we need to prepare and bake it fresh to order in our baker's oven.
reviews_data.review_text: The almond croissant was amazing. However, staff lacks proper training. I’m leaving this review in hopes that they improve their order system. I ordered a chai latte, and was never asked about milk options. Then, I ordered a breakfast sandwich without bacon, and she didn’t know if it could be done. After asking the kitchen, they said they could. When I got to the register, I had to list all the items I ordered. Like what? Why is it my job to list what I ordered!! That’s when I found out they had different milk options. After paying, I was told it would take 10 min for my croissant (10 min to remove bacon?!). I wish I had known that before, because I would have ordered something else. So I had to watch my husband eat while I was waiting.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Bacon Egg Cheese Croissant, Cinnamon Roll

reviews_data.review_text: Lucked up and found this gem. Everything is always fresh and made in house. They even have a spot where the kids can play quietly while you get your coffee fix.

Pre-made  breakfast , which was reheated. The sandwich was dry and cardboard like. The pastries are beautiful, but the taste is underwhelming. A cappuccino served in a paper cup is just not fitting. I would not return nor would I suggest to a friend..or enemy.
Absolutely amazing food. Best bakery in town.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Pan Au Chocolat, Croissant Selection, Apple Turnover Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: I was waiting for this authentic French Bakery to open🥳!! And it finally did! I visited twice now and I have to say that I love it! I tried couple of things and I'll be back for more🥖🥐🥪😋😊

Pretty unimpressed by our first experience here unfortunately. The food was just passable - the turkey salad is the only thing I’d order again. C'est magnifique,

I'm loathe to write this because I don't want everyone discovering the place and crowding it out...but, the owners are so nice and the place is so good I have to.

Before they opened I used to have to drive down to Charlotte to Renaissance to get real French pastries. Now, they're available right here at home.

The pastries are insanely good, the staff are all super nice and I can't wait to see it in the summer with outdoor seating.

We happened to be traveling through the area on our way down to Brunswick. We spent the night nearby and wanted something quick but not Starbucks or Panera. I found this place online and I don’t regret it. I’m only sad that I may not have the opportunity to return. The staff was very friendly and the food was amazing. I had the lox baguette and my husband had the egg and cheese croissant and a blueberry tarte. If you’re in the area, absolutely stop and try them out, you won’t regret it.

OMG - this is my new favorite bakery and restaurant. Fabulous service, oh so yummy food and great atmosphere. I’m so picky about breads and desserts. Great tasting, crusty bread. My stomach is happy😍
Can’t wait to come back.

Authentic french food - 10 stars.  Literally every thing on the menu that I have tried has tasted like I was in Paris.  From the bread, to the pastries, to the sandwiches - you can't go wrong here.  If there is a warm sourdough loaf by the register, buy it.  You won't regret it.

I do recommend to try their almond croissants - those are delicious.
An absolute beautiful venue and fantastic pastries and everything else!! Angela is the best!! A jewel!!

Beautiful. A perfect one word summation. The apple bowties are absolutely gorgeous 🥰 The lattes, delicious. A happy price point that if they increased too much more I'd probably just get a coffee so... Well thought out 😊 came in with a line to the door but they are quick, too!

reviews_data.review_text: Great experience!!  Very authentic artisan food.
Excellent food!

I came several times with the best hopes, and each time I left very disappointed. Each time, I gave this bakery another chance, telling myself that they had just opened and that not everything can go well right away. But nothing changed.

The atmosphere is not cozy at all; it feels like being at a railway station, and the place is dirty. The trays are unclean and covered in crumbs. You have to ask for silverware separately, as if it’s not obvious that you need it when you’re planning to eat. And the prices are too high for coffee in paper cups. Just an average spot with decent pastries.

Today, I asked for a hot coffee. They brought it barely warm, and after a few minutes, it was cold.

I nearly broke my teeth on this cube.

I do not recommend this place.

Wonderful to have an artisan bakery in our neighborhood. Thank you!!  I only wish there was a second checkout person for those of us that want to go quickly 15 minutes for a baguette seems a bit long. Also, I have to take a quick laugh of the reviewer below who said they wish they had a cinnamon roll. Clearly they’ve never been to Paris. There’s no such thing as a cinnamon roll in France! I wouldn’t be surprised if someone asked for chicken and waffles in this neighborhood lol!
Great food . Clean and fresh but just one super slow girl at the register. Need a better cashier or at least 2 registers . I spent more than 29 minutes just to pay . Need a better system

reviews_data.review_text: I came straight to cashier for Sourdough bread, then a crowd of 8-9 people walked in, I was told by cashier to get in line behind them, even though I was there before they all walked in. Frustrating as their breads are the best! I walked out, very disappointed 😞
Comfortable walking in, great service and atmosphere. The double espresso is bold and smooth, while the pastries are light, flaky, and delicious.

My friend and I stopped in here last weekend as we both appreciate some good French pastries. We tried the apple turnover croissant, pain suisse, pan au chocolat, and a strawberry fruit tart. Everything was visually stunning as you can see from the photos.

The croissants were both soft and crispy with a bunch of delicious fillings. Interestingly enough, the apple turnover croissant was filled with an applesauce mixture so you really get a lot of apple on this one! The pan au chocolat and the pain suisse also had some good fillings. As for the strawberry tart, the bottom had a nice shortbread cookie base, a lightly sweetened custard mixture, and super fresh strawberries. My friend was also tasting almond extract in this one, but I didn't get any taste of it. I'd say the apple turnover croissant is a winner in terms of creativity and taste.

The restaurant has both indoor and outdoor seating with friendly staff! It is a little noisy outside being right next to a busy road but they also have some cute seating indoors. There wasn't anything that knocked our socks off but all of the pastries were executed well and there is a good selection of pastries and breads to choose from.
A delightful French bakery. We had the breakfast croissant and gluten free breakfast wrap, almond croissant and sour dough bread with Swiss cheese.  They were all delicious!
Finally! A chocolate croissant that rivals some of the best I’ve had in France. Honestly it’s the best new spot in town. So happy Cocotte is here!

The cake part was chunky and fell apart. The icing was light and not too sweet but for a "freshly made" cupcake, it was already starting to have a hard shell. If they're sold out daily, it must be due to being "new". They are very expensive for this area (like European prices in Paris). Save your $$$ and visit another locally owned bakery.
Delicious food

Such a great experience   The food is extra delicious and the staff is so friendly and helpful   The almond croissants are beyond amazing as is the breakfast sandwich   Can’t wait to try their quiche Lorraine on my next visit   LOVE LOVE this place

This is an amazing bakery. The 77 north traffic makes it completely worth it. The very berry croissant is my favorite! Unfortunately it was seasonal but it should be year around. Their new seasonal dark chocolate cherry croissant is delicious and the passion fruit cube croissant. I have no complaints, hoping to try a tart soon!

French bakery in Cornelius. Friendly owners. Lovely community to go with a good bread loaf and yummy croissants!
The service was fast and excellent. The selections were just enough and the food was great.  We will be returning.

Not a good cafe at all. Not chill and cozy but instead all white no plants and hard benches. Give you a menu with around 25 things on it, but you can only get 5. Even though some people were there and the place looks big, it is just boring and depressing, not the right feel that I like. Don’t go here if you want to have a good experience. Everything I purchased was ‘’right on the money.‘’
Fresh and tasteful ❗
I am glad your business is here!
Food is super tasty. Perfectly flakey (you will have crumbs!) and buttery ratios on the croissant. The line is long but it moves fast. Staff is nice and very informative.

I had the Saint Germain which was excellent. It came with a side salad which was good., The baguette was extremely tasty I would definitely order this again.My desert was the absolute star of the meal. Can't remember the name but it consisted of croissant type of outer shell with a lemon curd and topped with meringue with lemon zest. It was wonderful. It was enough to split with someone., It is very well run, with employees who seem like they care about their jobs and customers. Wow.. I struggle to find words for how beautiful this bakery is.

I am a retired pastry chef who specialized in bread and laminated dough with over a decade of experience baking. THIS is the most exquisite, expertly crafted, technically perfect pastry I have ever seen. This level of craftsmanship you can usually only get if you travel to France. Luckily they've brought it right to our doorstep.

This is a special kind of food. One that requires time, love, precision, and care. The beauty of baking is that it is a science and a craft. In this establishment you can experience perfection; the absolute highest level of baking and pastry.

The atmosphere is clean and inviting. It is way bigger than I expected it to be. There are plenty of tables to sit at and an outside patio with giant picnic tables. The staff is friendly, attentive, and when they're not busy they're cleaning and restocking for the next rush. I love to see the teamwork and coordination. It is so refreshing to not see people just sitting on their phones when it isn't busy.

What more could we ask for as a community? Bakeries are a dying trade and I beg my fellow neighbors to come and support this business. I wish you guys all the success possible. You deserve it.

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently had the pleasure of stopping by Cocotte, a charming new French bakery and café that just opened in Cornelius. As soon as you walk in, you’re greeted by the irresistible aroma of freshly baked bread and pastries, all made from scratch right on the premises. One of the highlights is a window offering a direct view into the kitchen, where Chef Alexandre and his talented team work their magic throughout the day.

I decided to try the Versailles sandwich, a delightful combination of creamy French Brie, sweet fig jam, crisp lettuce, and savory prosciutto, all nestled in a perfectly baked baguette. It comes with a choice of side, and I opted for the turkey salad, which was a refreshing complement to the rich flavors of the sandwich.

Despite being newly opened, Cocotte has already started drawing a nice lunch crowd. A word of advice: if you visit later in the day, you might find they’ve sold out of some of their delicious offerings. So, plan to stop by around midday to ensure you get the full experience. Cocotte is truly a little slice of France right here in the Queen City, and it’s well worth a visit.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Merci Josephine! It was a pleasure to meet you and discuss with you. We're still working on getting our full menu, and we're almost there! I invite you to swing by again when our wonderful pastry chefs will present all the classics and their signatures patisseries. Many have been asking for macarons, eclairs and Paris-Brest. All coming soon!

Just discovered this cafe in Huntersville, and I am in awe! It is an “Artisan French Bakery” and man do they deliver! I’ve been to France before and everything they serve is authentic. Her statement, “This may be the best breakfast croissant I’ve ever had.” Their offerings are varied, beautiful and tasty. 11/10 recommend!

Cocotte is such a charming bakery! The pastries are always fresh and delicious. A special thanks to Jenny for her kind and attentive service – she makes every visit even better!

BEST BAKERY!!! Pastries and breads that taste even better than they look. Our whole family loves their breakfast croissants as well.
So thrilled there’s a French bakery in town!

Wow! What beautiful pastries and treats! Mesmerizing for the eyes and divine for the nose. We tried the Apple bow tie, Madeline’s, Olive and Rosemary baguette, of course chocolate croissants! And tasty coffee treats ☕️ Heading back tomorrow morning. A must try!

This is by far the best addition to the Lake Norman area. The coffee selection and quality is amazing. The food and pastry options are delicious! Anytime friends come to town. This is our new go to place
Attention dog owners. No pup cups.
This place is the real deal when it comes to bakeries. Everything I’ve tried has been delicious and you can tell it’s made by hand.
Incredible! The croissants are amazing and everything I have tried has been wonderful! So happy to have this lovely French bakery in Cornelius!

A truly authentic French patisserie - so glad we have one here in the Lake Norman area! The pastries and breads made here are top notch - you’d be pressed to find this level of quality outside of a high-end European cafe this side of the Atlantic. The staff are friendly and the atmosphere is inviting. On the weekends there is always a line outside. The wait is 100% worth it!

Dirty and Rude – Won’t Be Returning

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Marcie

We wanted to let you know that we had to make an exceptional modification to the apple bowtie filling on Sunday. Unfortunately, the result wasn’t up to our usual standards, and we truly regret that. Recommend: Chocolate Croissant, Breakfast Sandwich, and Chocolate Chunk Cookie

reviews_data.owner_answer:

reviews_data.review_text: Every single item I have tasted is amazing! Not only delicious beyond words the pastries and breads are beautiful in presentation. So happy to have a Cocotte in the neighborhood.

reviews_data.review_text:
For my first visit, I picked up a few pastries to take home and a tea latte. The number of choices was a bit overwhelming, to be honest!

I did have to wait a good bit for my drink, extra because of an error with the drink, actually twice, but I didn't correct the second error because I needed to get home.

But, the time I waited gave me a chance to browse the for sale items, outside of the bakery items, and the variety of seating, including a children's area with some toys and books.  At least one booth had a plug if you need to work for a bit and there is Wi-Fi.

I was excited to see a place with a variety of tea and tea lattes; however, the seasonal latte I ordered was first given to me as an iced coffee. I don't drink coffee, so I asked to correct the drink. I was given an iced tea drink that was OK BUT it was not a latte. No milk!

The best pastries I tried were the apple bow tie and blueberry brioche bun. The chocolate cream croissant didn't have much filling and the lemon meringue pie slice had kind of a sticky texture?

Some of the items are a reasonable price but others are a little on the high side, so my review is a little mixed.
🤩 wow, what a find! C’est manufique!! If you want authentic French breads and amazing pastries and desserts, come here. They have so many options. Gotta go again!

C’est magnifique!!

Cinq étoiles!!
The best pastries I’ve ever had. Everything looks so good, the decision is overwhelming.
Best breads and pastries! 🥐🥖🍞🍰😋
Everything is absolutely delicious here!
Unbelievable bakery with the most delicious chocolate croissant it was gone in 30 seconds.

We absolutely love Cocotte!  I stopped in to grab some pastries on Saturday for Mother's Day and although there was a line, it moved quickly. I picked up a couple almond croissant (light,  flaky & wonderful almond flavor), a few macaroons (scrumptious) and a couple of eclairs (yummy chocolate-WOW!).  Once I arrived home (around 4:00), I decided to place an online order for a couple of cinnamon rolls and chocolate croissants to pick up the following morning. Unfortunately, they did not have this available as I missed the 12:00 cut off (completely my fault!)  They were more than gracious to offer a refund or a choice of other pastry items. Of course, I chose the pastry items, and I have to say they over-compensated for MY mistake!  Needless to say, everything was incredibly fresh and delicious. Such lovely, friendly & accommodating staff and mouthwatering baked goods. We used to drive down to Charlotte for fresh French pastries. So glad we have this incredible gem in Cornelius now!!

Absolutely exceptional. You can tell they really take pride in everything they do and the ingredients they use. The pastries are fantastic and look immaculate. We have tried multiple different drinks and they have all been very good. Once you go once you will keep going back.

Food was really disappointing. I felt fooled that the pictures made everything look so good. All of the sandwiches were pre-made and kept in a refrigerator which makes the bread go extremely hard and chewy. Ive had airport sandwiches that tasted fresher. If the food was prepared to order as the menu makes it seem it could probably be 10x better. The chickpea side salad was oily and bland. Pastry was dry and tasted 2 days old and the custard had such an artificial taste behind it. We barely ate any of the food and it wasn't cheap. Service was slow and unhelpful too. This place has potential as the customer vibe was good and the bread loaves looked great but refrigerating the pre-made sandwiches is ruining it.
Awesome food and great service!

Love this place! The coffee, every pastry and OMG the quiche is like no other I've ever had. Can't seem to go wrong with anything I've had from there. Also, I recommend getting there early, they do run out.

Excellent bakery

reviews_data.review_text: This is a Saturday morning must for espresso and croissant! Everything is amazing!

The pastries of this place are like no other, total perfection. We did not have a real bakery in this area and I am delighted that Cocotte opened here. I truly believe that the mediocre reviews done here are posted by some competition bakery. Someone mentioned they couldn't find anything with cinnamon? You can find cinnamon pretty much in everything in the U.S, so for that you can go to get a pastry at any supermarket. Cocotte is the closest to a real French bakery that you can find in Cornelius/Huntersville, NC.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Bonjour Kim, we're happy to read you loved our food! To answer your comment about the service, I'd like you to understand that the person who served you started on Saturday. Assuming you swung by this weekend, it was probably her first or second day at the bakery. We usually do not ask our hundreds of customers their choice of milk (we default to whole milk if not specified). reviews_data.review_text: The almond croissant was amazing. However, staff lacks proper training. I’m leaving this review in hopes that they improve their order system. After asking the kitchen, they said they could. When I got to the register, I had to list all the items I ordered. Like what? Why is it my job to list what I ordered!! That’s when I found out they had different milk options. After paying, I was told it would take 10 min for my croissant (10 min to remove bacon?!). Comfortable walking in, great service and atmosphere. The double espresso is bold and smooth, while the pastries are light, flaky, and delicious.

My friend and I stopped in here last weekend as we both appreciate some good French pastries. We tried the apple turnover croissant, pain suisse, pan au chocolat, and a strawberry fruit tart. Everything was visually stunning as you can see from the photos.

The croissants were both soft and crispy with a bunch of delicious fillings. Interestingly enough, the apple turnover croissant was filled with an applesauce mixture so you really get a lot of apple on this one! The pan au chocolat and the pain suisse also had some good fillings. As for the strawberry tart, the bottom had a nice shortbread cookie base, a lightly sweetened custard mixture, and super fresh strawberries. My friend was also tasting almond extract in this one, but I didn't get any taste of it. I'd say the apple turnover croissant is a winner in terms of creativity and taste.

The restaurant has both indoor and outdoor seating with friendly staff! It is a little noisy outside being right next to a busy road but they also have some cute seating indoors. There wasn't anything that knocked our socks off but all of the pastries were executed well and there is a good selection of pastries and breads to choose from.
A delightful French bakery. We had the breakfast croissant and gluten free breakfast wrap, almond croissant and sour dough bread with Swiss cheese.  They were all delicious!
Finally! A chocolate croissant that rivals some of the best I’ve had in France. Honestly it’s the best new spot in town. So happy Cocotte is here!

Wow.. I struggle to find words for how beautiful this bakery is.

I am a retired pastry chef who specialized in bread and laminated dough with over a decade of experience baking. THIS is the most exquisite, expertly crafted, technically perfect pastry I have ever seen. This level of craftsmanship you can usually only get if you travel to France. Luckily they've brought it right to our doorstep.

This is a special kind of food. One that requires time, love, precision, and care. The beauty of baking is that it is a science and a craft. In this establishment you can experience perfection; the absolute highest level of baking and pastry.

The atmosphere is clean and inviting. It is way bigger than I expected it to be. There are plenty of tables to sit at and an outside patio with giant picnic tables. The staff is friendly, attentive, and when they're not busy they're cleaning and restocking for the next rush. I love to see the teamwork and coordination. It is so refreshing to not see people just sitting on their phones when it isn't busy.

Here you will find fresh artisan breads, perfectly laminated croissants, pastries, sandwiches, home made sides, and of course our own locally roasted Defined Coffee. What more could we ask for as a community? Bakeries are a dying trade and I beg my fellow neighbors to come and support this business. You can't and won't find this kind of shop anywhere else in charlotte. I've looked.

I wish you guys all the success possible. You deserve it.

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently had the pleasure of stopping by Cocotte, a charming new French bakery and café that just opened in Cornelius. As soon as you walk in, you’re greeted by the irresistible aroma of freshly baked bread and pastries, all made from scratch right on the premises. One of the highlights is a window offering a direct view into the kitchen, where Chef Alexandre and his talented team work their magic throughout the day.

I decided to try the Versailles sandwich, a delightful combination of creamy French Brie, sweet fig jam, crisp lettuce, and savory prosciutto, all nestled in a perfectly baked baguette. It comes with a choice of side, and I opted for the turkey salad, which was a refreshing complement to the rich flavors of the sandwich.

Despite being newly opened, Cocotte has already started drawing a nice lunch crowd. A word of advice: if you visit later in the day, you might find they’ve sold out of some of their delicious offerings. So, plan to stop by around midday to ensure you get the full experience. Cocotte is truly a little slice of France right here in the Queen City, and it’s well worth a visit.

All coming soon!
